<div class="main-content">
    <div class="content">
        <h1>How to Create a Reverse Shell</h1>
        <p>
            Some CTF Challenges like pyjail can sometimes need a revshell to get the flag.
            This tutorial will help you to create a revshell that you can interact in your terminal.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Reverse Shell Using Pinggy</h2>
        
        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">1</span>
            <h3 class="step-title">Start a Local Netcat Listener</h3>
            <div class="step-content">
                <img src="/images/revshell-step-1.png" alt="Pinggy website" class="step-image">
                <p>Start a local netcat server by doing this command, `nc -lnvp 4000` or any other port you want.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">2</span>
            <h3 class="step-title">Visit Pinggy Website</h3>
            <div class="step-content">
                <img src="/images/server-step-1.png" alt="Pinggy website" class="step-image">
                <p>Go to <a href="https://pinggy.io/"> Pinggy</a> and configure the local address to point to your localhost web server.</p>
                <div class="tip">Make sure to use TCP protocol. Typically the connection made by revshell is a TCP connection</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">3</span>
            <h3 class="step-title">Start the Tunneling Service</h3>
            <div class="step-content">
                <img src="/images/server-step-2.png" alt="Pinggy website" class="step-image">
                <p>
                    Copy the command and paste it to your terminal. 
                    This will create a tunnel connecting your localhost server to a public IP address. 
                    It will give you the public url to be used when making the revshell.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">4</span>
            <h3 class="step-title">Create the Reverse Shell Payload</h3>
            <div class="step-content">
                <img src="/images/revshell-step-2.png" alt="Pinggy website" class="step-image">
                <p>
                    Visit this <a href="https://www.revshells.com/">reverse shell generator</a> and put the public url and port.
                    Choose a suitable payload for your CTF challenge.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <span class="step-number">5</span>
            <h3 class="step-title">Send the payload</h3>
            <div class="step-content">
                <p>Send the created payload to your target and we will have a reverse shell</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sidebar">
        <h3>What You'll Need</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>nc command</li>
            <li>Tunneling Service (ngrok, Pinggy, etc)</li>
            <li>Wifi Connection</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Difficulty Level</h3>
